The out-of-scope features define the functionalities that are not included in the Smart Queue Management System for Banks. These limitations help maintain a clear project boundary and avoid scope creep.
Out-of-Scope Features
1.	Online Banking Transactions
The system will not handle money transfers, deposits, withdrawals, or payments.
2.	Loan and Account Processing
Loan approvals, account creation, and KYC verification are not covered.
3.	ATM and Cash Machine Services
Queue management for ATMs is excluded.
4.	Appointment Scheduling
Advance appointment booking is not supported.
5.	Hospital or Non-Banking Services
The system is strictly limited to bank branch queue management.
6.	Customer Data Analytics Beyond Basic Reports
Advanced analytics and AI-based predictions are not included.
7.	Third-Party Financial System Integration
Integration with core banking or external financial platforms is excluded.
